cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA 

The paper deals with designing algorithms for online decision-making in adversarial environments, which is a common topic in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The use of dynamic programming and convex optimization techniques also suggests a possible fit in the optimization and control (cs.DS) category. Finally, the focus on repeated games and strategies for achieving minimal guarantees suggests a possible fit in the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) category.
